title: Presidio of San Francisco: Stories
body: Stories        Tent camp in the Main Post area of the Presidio during the Spanish American War. The influx of troops to the Presidio during the Spanish American and Philippine wars forever changed the face of the Presidio. U.S. Military History Institute   Â    The Presidio's stories reflect the dynamic history of our county from even before the year of its inception. From internal wars, to the wars that led to the country's status as a superpower, the lives of a multitude of people have been touched by the events in which the Presidio played a role. Use the links to the left to learn more about these stories.
